Rob you start.

00:25:56.310 --> 00:25:58.820
&gt;&gt; Rob: [Inaudible]
it's an honor for us

00:25:58.820 --> 00:26:01.770
to be here today at New Day.

00:26:01.770 --> 00:26:04.050
It's an honor for us to
be here in New Day USA,

00:26:04.050 --> 00:26:08.250
and be supportive of, of
the Gold Star families.

00:26:08.250 --> 00:26:13.500
And I guess a question
that I would have is,

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:16.760
what could companies like
New Day and the community

00:26:16.760 --> 00:26:20.300
to do more, to help
more Gold Star families?

00:26:20.300 --> 00:26:25.910
Because I think that [inaudible]
General Caldwell this,

00:26:25.910 --> 00:26:29.480
this school that he has, at
Georgia Military College,

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:35.210
it's really an amazing, an
amazing place to raise children.

00:26:35.210 --> 00:26:39.410
And I think that any child
that's a son or daughter

00:26:39.410 --> 00:26:42.060
of a Gold Star family, it
would just be incredible

00:26:42.060 --> 00:26:45.400
if we could be helping
more Gold Star families.

00:26:45.400 --> 00:26:49.360
In terms of, if we're on the
phone, the Admiral Tyler Lynch,

00:26:49.360 --> 00:26:51.630
our Chairman and
myself are on the phone

00:26:51.630 --> 00:26:53.170
with many Gold Star families.

00:26:53.170 --> 00:27:01.620
And you know, we, we have some
understanding of, of the pain

00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:05.770
and sacrifice just from our
conversations that we have

00:27:05.770 --> 00:27:07.240
with Gold Star families.

00:27:07.240 --> 00:27:10.260
And one of the things
that we see is

00:27:10.260 --> 00:27:13.590
that if we can help the children
of these Gold Star families be

00:27:13.590 --> 00:27:17.110
in the right environment for
high school, it's not a question

00:27:17.110 --> 00:27:18.410
of college, because a lot

00:27:18.410 --> 00:27:21.220
of these Gold Star children
never get to college.

00:27:21.220 --> 00:27:25.240
And if we can get them
a boost and a step up,

00:27:25.240 --> 00:27:28.570
in terms of getting them
the right education,

00:27:28.570 --> 00:27:31.560
then more, very positive.

00:27:31.560 --> 00:27:35.540
So what can we do to find
more Gold Star families,

00:27:35.540 --> 00:27:38.780
help more Gold Star children,
and what can the community do,

00:27:38.780 --> 00:27:43.180
not just obviously New
Day, to, to help educate?

00:27:43.180 --> 00:27:46.630
I think the education is the
greatest gift we can give

00:27:46.630 --> 00:27:49.310
in terms of healing for
these Gold Star families,

00:27:49.310 --> 00:27:50.610
but thank you Mort.

00:27:50.610 --> 00:27:51.910
&gt;&gt; Mort Dean: Yeah thank you.

00:27:51.910 --> 00:27:53.210
Go ahead.

00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:54.510
&gt;&gt; Bonnie Carroll:
Thank you so much Rob,

00:27:54.510 --> 00:27:55.810
thank you for everything
that New Day does.

00:27:55.810 --> 00:28:00.820
And thank you for being here,
and you're absolutely right.

00:28:00.820 --> 00:28:04.600
The children of America's fallen
heroes have been given federal

00:28:04.600 --> 00:28:06.580
benefits through the
Department of Veterans Affairs

00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:09.610
to expand the GI bill,
the Frye Scholarship.

00:28:09.610 --> 00:28:12.020
There are also state
waivers of fees and tuition

00:28:12.020 --> 00:28:15.470
and private scholarships
and programs like yours.

00:28:15.470 --> 00:28:17.060
It's absolutely essential

00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:20.610
that we let the families
know in an organized way.

00:28:20.610 --> 00:28:23.780
I work very closely with
all of our partner VSOs

00:28:23.780 --> 00:28:25.490
and military service
organizations.

00:28:25.490 --> 00:28:28.800
And through TAPS we
have an education portal

00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:33.010
that families can go in, log
in, and get a list of everything

00:28:33.010 --> 00:28:35.490
that they're available,
that they're eligible for.

00:28:35.490 --> 00:28:38.710
And then we help them
work through that

00:28:38.710 --> 00:28:41.480
so that they can figure
out what's the right way

00:28:41.480 --> 00:28:44.000
to structure their
benefit's to meet their goals,

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:46.050
their educational goals.

00:28:46.050 --> 00:28:48.220
I appreciate we, we've
worked with you all

00:28:48.220 --> 00:28:52.260
and it's good to
see you again sir.

00:28:52.260 --> 00:28:57.280
And it is absolutely essential
that we get the benefit's

00:28:57.280 --> 00:28:59.180
and the resources
that are available

00:28:59.180 --> 00:29:01.580
to the families to them.

00:29:01.580 --> 00:29:03.670
That's one of the goals
that the TAPS has.

00:29:03.670 --> 00:29:07.710
So it's at TAPS.org,
the education portal.

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:12.230
And we've got to reach
every Gold Star family

00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:15.520
and let them know that
there is support available

00:29:15.520 --> 00:29:16.920
and there are resources

00:29:16.920 --> 00:29:19.760
for education services,
absolutely essential.

00:29:19.760 --> 00:29:21.060
So thank you.

00:29:21.060 --> 00:29:23.430
&gt;&gt; Becky Christmas: I'd
like to add to that also.

00:29:23.430 --> 00:29:28.300
I think that can also reach out
to all the other organizations

00:29:28.300 --> 00:29:31.120
in addition to TAPS, but
Gold Star Wives of America,

00:29:31.120 --> 00:29:35.390
American Gold Star Mothers,
because we do have services

00:29:35.390 --> 00:29:40.160
that we provide for veterans and
we, we don't always have the,

00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:42.850
the manpower or the way to
get all that information out.

00:29:42.850 --> 00:29:46.830
So we're volunteering in the
VA hospitals, and we see needs

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:48.670
for the veterans
in the hospitals.

00:29:48.670 --> 00:29:52.230
Clothing, maybe newspaper
subscriptions,

00:29:52.230 --> 00:29:54.620
maybe laptops, things like that.

00:29:54.620 --> 00:29:57.950
We volunteer in the
clinics, in small communities

00:29:57.950 --> 00:30:00.420
like where I come from.

00:30:00.420 --> 00:30:03.920
We, we go, we sit in the,
in the waiting room visiting

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:07.660
with veterans, and they'll
tell you their story,

00:30:07.660 --> 00:30:11.730
and they will tell you what they
need or what their barriers are

00:30:11.730 --> 00:30:15.530
that they're trying to
overcome, to get benefit's or,

00:30:15.530 --> 00:30:19.160
or just everyday living
things that they need.

00:30:19.160 --> 00:30:23.400
And so we, we try to help them
with the sources they need,

00:30:23.400 --> 00:30:25.720
or the direction
to go get those.

00:30:25.720 --> 00:30:27.800
But sometimes they don't
have a strong enough voice

00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:30.730
as I was saying, to, so
we sometimes have to go

00:30:30.730 --> 00:30:33.050
with them personally
to do those things.

00:30:33.050 --> 00:30:35.790
We also volunteer in VA centers

00:30:35.790 --> 00:30:39.600
where of course a veteran is
going to come to find out,

00:30:39.600 --> 00:30:41.550
you know, what benefit's
he might get,

00:30:41.550 --> 00:30:44.180
or help get his paperwork
in order,

00:30:44.180 --> 00:30:46.420
and we try to steer
them that way.

00:30:46.420 --> 00:30:50.490
But then we work with stand
down, homeless veterans.

00:30:50.490 --> 00:30:54.140
When you go to a stand down,
and you see the veterans

00:30:54.140 --> 00:30:57.710
on the street and the fact
that they need a haircut,

00:30:57.710 --> 00:31:00.950
they need a dental exam
and all of those things,

00:31:00.950 --> 00:31:05.000
there are resources there
that, that we, we really need

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:07.460
to help those, those veterans.

00:31:07.460 --> 00:31:09.160
The families of the fallen,

00:31:09.160 --> 00:31:13.420
sometimes when the
initial casualty officer is

00:31:13.420 --> 00:31:16.310
with the families of, of
a family of the fallen,

00:31:16.310 --> 00:31:20.270
and then they're gone, and maybe
they don't remain in contact,

00:31:20.270 --> 00:31:22.990
a few-- for me I
know it was two years

00:31:22.990 --> 00:31:26.460
down the road before I really
was ready to even talk about a,

00:31:26.460 --> 00:31:30.440
an organization where I
could volunteer my services.

00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:34.830
So we need to, we need to make
sure those families maintain

00:31:34.830 --> 00:31:38.230
that information and
know who to contact.

00:31:38.230 --> 00:31:39.740
And they don't always do that.

00:31:39.740 --> 00:31:41.750
They, they've lost the
paperwork, you know,

00:31:41.750 --> 00:31:43.260
for if they're a wife.

00:31:43.260 --> 00:31:46.760
They, they, you know, they
may have children and they,

00:31:46.760 --> 00:31:48.560
that's what they've had
to concentrate on and

00:31:48.560 --> 00:31:52.160
yet they need something for
themselves, people to talk to.

00:31:52.160 --> 00:31:53.790
So maybe they need
an organization

00:31:53.790 --> 00:31:57.680
like Gold Star wives or a mother
needs someone else to talk

00:31:57.680 --> 00:32:01.480
to that's besides her
husband, you know about,

00:32:01.480 --> 00:32:02.990
because they're sharing
that grief.

00:32:02.990 --> 00:32:06.850
So those, the information
about the organizations,

00:32:06.850 --> 00:32:11.140
the actual physical work that
we need to do for our veterans,

00:32:11.140 --> 00:32:16.040
those things are sources,
resources that we really need.

00:32:16.040 --> 00:32:17.340
&gt;&gt; Mort Dean: Yes ma'am.

00:32:17.340 --> 00:32:22.120
&gt;&gt; Mona Gun: I don't need a
mike I don't think I have a

00:32:22.120 --> 00:32:23.980
loud voice.

00:32:23.980 --> 00:32:25.280
&gt;&gt; Mort Dean: We
all need a mike.

00:32:25.280 --> 00:32:30.110
&gt;&gt; Mona Gun: I am Mona
Gun, I'm a Gold Star mom.

00:32:30.110 --> 00:32:35.480
And my son pre-9/11, one of
the sailors that was killed

00:32:35.480 --> 00:32:38.630
on board the USS Cole, so I
appreciate what you've done

00:32:38.630 --> 00:32:41.530
if you're reported
on that bombing.

00:32:41.530 --> 00:32:46.030
That pre-9/11 families
are sometimes left

00:32:46.030 --> 00:32:47.810
out of many, many things.

00:32:47.810 --> 00:32:52.890
And my son was not married,
he was a single young many

00:32:52.890 --> 00:32:55.530
who followed dad's footsteps.

00:32:55.530 --> 00:32:56.830
Went into the Navy

00:32:56.830 --> 00:33:00.110
and my husband had a 21 year
very successful Navy career

00:33:00.110 --> 00:33:03.380
and my son, nine
months and he was gone.

00:33:03.380 --> 00:33:05.700
And our family was
torn apart, you know.

00:33:05.700 --> 00:33:08.210
I have three other sons.

00:33:08.210 --> 00:33:12.750
My oldest son found a way
to deal with his grief.

00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:17.290
Sharom who was killed had
two younger brothers, twins.

00:33:17.290 --> 00:33:20.180
My boys were in college
during that time.

00:33:20.180 --> 00:33:23.840
There's very little out
there for siblings, and for,

00:33:23.840 --> 00:33:25.640
for parents and families,

00:33:25.640 --> 00:33:30.330
when there is a single
service member that is killed.

00:33:30.330 --> 00:33:34.370
Of course the VA, the Department
of Defense, are right there

00:33:34.370 --> 00:33:39.620
for spouses and for the children
of fallen, but siblings there,

00:33:39.620 --> 00:33:40.920
there was very little.

00:33:40.920 --> 00:33:44.300
My boys, to this
day, were in college

00:33:44.300 --> 00:33:46.270
and have not finished
their degree.

00:33:46.270 --> 00:33:50.280
Mom's got two degrees,
daddy got two degrees.

00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:54.850
So any kind of support that
you can give for siblings,

00:33:54.850 --> 00:33:59.000
I don't know if you're aware
of any sibling programs

00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:04.770
that will provide
college support will be

00:34:04.770 --> 00:34:06.220
greatly appreciated.

00:34:06.220 --> 00:34:08.910
I have found-- I
found Gold Star Moms

00:34:08.910 --> 00:34:13.520
that helped me tremendously,
my oldest son did some things

00:34:13.520 --> 00:34:17.840
to keep alive the
service of his brother.

00:34:17.840 --> 00:34:21.860
But my boys, the twins, to this
day are still dealing with,

00:34:21.860 --> 00:34:24.550
and it will be 18 years for us.

00:34:24.550 --> 00:34:28.010
They were in college, so if you
know of any programs out there,

00:34:28.010 --> 00:34:31.120
if you all know of any
programs or any things out there

00:34:31.120 --> 00:34:35.050
that could support
siblings is critical.

00:34:35.050 --> 00:34:36.350
&gt;&gt; Mort Dean: Thank you.

00:34:36.350 --> 00:34:40.110
Is, is there a, a list or
somewhere where people can go

00:34:40.110 --> 00:34:41.410
who have questions like that?

00:34:41.410 --> 00:34:42.710
&gt;&gt; Jenine Melton: Well we have
a sibling and it's very true,

00:34:42.710 --> 00:34:45.150
because there were not a
lot of things out there.

00:34:45.150 --> 00:34:49.410
And since I've recently gotten
more involved into TAPS,

00:34:49.410 --> 00:34:52.530
I joined what's called
a Peer Mentor Program.

00:34:52.530 --> 00:34:55.000
And that's a program
where we do some training,

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:57.460
and then they assign
you with a peer mentor

00:34:57.460 --> 00:34:59.630
who has experienced
a similar loss.

00:34:59.630 --> 00:35:02.410
And it's essentially
a network of siblings

00:35:02.410 --> 00:35:04.390
that support each other.

00:35:04.390 --> 00:35:08.800
We also have routine calls where
we have webcasts where we talk

00:35:08.800 --> 00:35:12.150
and communicate with each
other, and support, and just try

00:35:12.150 --> 00:35:13.740
to establish that outreach.

00:35:13.740 --> 00:35:16.280
So I would say TAPS has
done an excellent job

00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:17.920
in establishing that program.

00:35:17.920 --> 00:35:21.160
And then also they have other
programs within the summertime

00:35:21.160 --> 00:35:23.940
where they have certain things
for siblings, for camps,

00:35:23.940 --> 00:35:27.380
and other activities and
outreach things that you can do.

00:35:27.380 --> 00:35:29.270
And I know also with
the Maryland Chapter

00:35:29.270 --> 00:35:31.910
of Gold Star Mothers, I've
gotten involved with some

00:35:31.910 --> 00:35:33.940
of the other siblings
there trying to partner

00:35:33.940 --> 00:35:35.830
and do other outreach
things that we can do

00:35:35.830 --> 00:35:37.590
in honor of our fallen heroes.

00:35:37.590 --> 00:35:40.430
So that's one thing that I'm
really trying to make sure

00:35:40.430 --> 00:35:43.080
that I try to lean forward
on and trying to get involved

00:35:43.080 --> 00:35:45.090
with the TAPS program,
doing things

00:35:45.090 --> 00:35:46.870
with the American
Gold Star Mothers.

00:35:46.870 --> 00:35:49.820
And then even things
within our community to try

00:35:49.820 --> 00:35:52.710
to bring more siblings in
because sometimes we do feel

00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:55.200
like we have been forgotten.

00:35:55.200 --> 00:35:57.570
But I'm glad to see
that programs like TAP

00:35:57.570 --> 00:35:59.490
and the American Gold
Star Mothers is starting

00:35:59.490 --> 00:36:01.810
to wrap their arms
around the siblings

00:36:01.810 --> 00:36:04.140
and saying we haven't
forgotten you, we love you

00:36:04.140 --> 00:36:05.440
and we're here for you.

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:07.320
So that's what I'm
personally trying to do.

00:36:07.320 --> 00:36:09.740
I'm making sure that I
make other siblings aware

00:36:09.740 --> 00:36:12.510
of these programs to
support each other.

00:36:12.510 --> 00:36:13.810
&gt;&gt; Mort Dean: That's great.

