00:53:30.740 --> 00:53:35.130
They're basically creating
this oral and visual history

00:53:35.130 --> 00:53:39.880
of service, and all kinds
of service, combat service,

00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:48.030
service in war time, free time,
whenever, service is service.

00:53:48.030 --> 00:53:52.460
And they asked us, as part
of this agreement that we,

00:53:52.460 --> 00:53:55.620
and cooperation that we
currently have going,

00:53:55.620 --> 00:53:57.380
to see if we could put
together some things.

00:53:57.380 --> 00:54:00.220
And New Day is, is very humbled,
and we're always humbled

00:54:00.220 --> 00:54:02.420
with every opportunity we
have to connect with people

00:54:02.420 --> 00:54:05.760
in our community, especially
the families of those who serve.

00:54:05.760 --> 00:54:09.740
Unfortunately their
stories often go untold.

00:54:09.740 --> 00:54:11.900
That is why I'm grateful
to the Library of Congress

00:54:11.900 --> 00:54:14.300
and the Veterans History
Project for allowing us to reach

00:54:14.300 --> 00:54:17.430
out to these individuals
and tell these stories

00:54:17.430 --> 00:54:18.740
that our community
and our nation

00:54:18.740 --> 00:54:21.250
as a whole will better
understand the history

00:54:21.250 --> 00:54:22.940
of our nation.

00:54:22.940 --> 00:54:26.680
We may never be able to fully
repay our veterans for all

00:54:26.680 --> 00:54:28.630
that they have done,
but this projects,

00:54:28.630 --> 00:54:31.440
the Veterans History Project
is a great way to acknowledge

00:54:31.440 --> 00:54:33.800
and to genuinely honor
these men and women

00:54:33.800 --> 00:54:37.500
by archiving their
firsthand members, memories,

00:54:37.500 --> 00:54:39.330
with the Library of Congress.

00:54:39.330 --> 00:54:42.260
Today we have brought
with us the first

00:54:42.260 --> 00:54:44.780
of what will be many interviews

00:54:44.780 --> 00:54:49.160
that New Day USA will
complete, yes complete.

00:54:49.160 --> 00:54:52.790
And this is a testimony of
service, and long service

00:54:52.790 --> 00:54:56.680
and distinguished service of
Rear Admiral Thomas Lynch,

00:54:56.680 --> 00:54:59.280
our chairman, and we
are pleased to turn

00:54:59.280 --> 00:55:03.240
in this Living Touchstone over
to the Veterans History Project.

00:55:03.240 --> 00:55:05.510
And I'll let Admiral
Lynch do that.

